1. Purpose
This project is a simple library website allowing users to:
Register an account
Log in / log out
Search and reserve books (by title or category)
View and un-reserve their reserved books
2. Technologies Used
PHP (backend)
MySQL database (database name: Bookdb)
HTML + CSS for frontend
Session-based authentication
3. Setup Instructions
Clone the repository.
Set up a local web server (e.g., XAMPP, WAMP, LAMP) with PHP and MySQL.
Create the database schema with the following tables:
   - users: username, password, firstname, surname, addressline, addressline2, city, telephone, mobile, passwordcomfer
   - books: ISBN, booktitle, author, reserved, categoryID
   - reservations: username, ISBN, reservedDate
In db.php, update the database credentials (host, username, password, database name).
   Default configuration: host='localhost', username='root', password='', database='Bookdb'
Place the project in the web server's root (e.g., htdocs or www).
Access via browser, e.g., http://localhost/Library-Website/index.html.
4. File Structure (key files)
index.html — Welcome / landing page with links to login and registration.
registration.php — Handles user registration with form validation.
login.php — Handles user login with session management.
login_homepage.php — User's homepage after successful login with navigation links.
reservation.php — Book reservation interface with search by title or category (8 categories: Health, Business, Biography, Technology, Travel, Self-Help, Cookery, Fiction).
logout.php — Handles user logout and session destruction.
db.php — Database connection file (connects to Bookdb database).
main.css — Styling.
viewreg.php — Displays current user's reserved books and allows unreserving.
usernotloged.html — Prompts users to log in before accessing restricted features.
test_reserve_form.html — Test form for book reservation functionality.
